The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 01 May is 41,922 (4,852.2 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 26 April, there were 133 new confirmed cases (15.4 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 19 April, there were 136 new cases, and so the new cases have decreased by 2% (3 fewer cases).
